---
import DiagnosticEntryLayer from "../components/DiagnosticEntryLayer.astro";
import { diagnosticEntries } from "../data/diagnosticEntries";
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Meta-Writing Ecology"
  description="Meta-Writing Ecology is a recursive linguistic system and structural diagnostic framework."
>
  <section>
    <h1>Meta-Writing Ecology</h1>

    <p class="lede">
      Meta-Writing Ecology is a recursive linguistic system and structural
      diagnostic framework.
    </p>

    <p>
      It is not ecological science, environmental research, biodiversity
      analysis, environmental writing, or a writing-advice project.
    </p>

    <p>
      Its purpose is to make structural behavior visible: how texts shape later
      texts, how instructions constrain outputs, and how meaning reorganizes
      under pressure.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Start Here</h2>

    <ul>
      <li><a href="/about/">About the System</a></li>
      <li><a href="/zh/">中文導讀｜語寫生態</a></li>
      <li><a href="/surfaces/">Entry Surfaces</a></li>
      <li><a href="/boundary/">Public Boundary</a></li>
      <li><a href="/site-notes/">Public Site Notes</a></li>
      <li><a href="/public-records/">Public Record Anchors</a></li>
      <li><a href="/public-version-notes/">Public Version Notes</a></li>
      <li><a href="/public-surface-map/">Public Surface Map</a></li>
      <li><a href="/document-types/">Document Types</a></li>
      <li><a href="/citation-guide/">Citation Guide</a></li>
      <li><a href="/entry-points/">Thematic Entry Points</a></li>
      <li><a href="/ai-reading-guide/">AI Reading Guide</a></li>
      <li><a href="/ai-readable-knowledge-architecture/">AI-Readable Knowledge Architecture</a></li>
      <li><a href="/atlas/">Model Atlas</a></li>
      <li><a href="/models/">Selected Public Model Clusters</a></li>
      <li><a href="/fiction/">Fiction / Narrative Overflow</a></li>
      <li><a href="/publications/">Publications and DOI Records</a></li>
      <li><a href="/platforms/">Platforms</a></li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Diagnostic Entry Layer</h2>

    <p>
      A low-commitment entry layer for readers asking whether a problem they
      are seeing may fall within the descriptive range of Meta-Writing Ecology.
    </p>

    <p>
      This is not a solution layer, audit, policy recommendation, or complete
      diagnosis. Each entry moves from an observed problem surface to possible
      structural patterns, related documents, and boundary reminders.
    </p>

    <p>
      <a class="diagnostic-entry-link" href="/diagnostic-entry-layer/">
        Explore diagnostic entries
      </a>
    </p>

    <DiagnosticEntryLayer
      entries={diagnosticEntries}
      compact={true}
      limit={3}
      showControls={false}
    />
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Public Reading Paths</h2>

    <p>
      For fiction readers:
      Start with <a href="/fiction/">Fiction / Narrative Overflow</a>.
    </p>

    <p>
      For research and citation:
      Start with <a href="/publications/">Publications and DOI Records</a>
      and <a href="/citation-guide/">Citation Guide</a>.
    </p>

    <p>
      For AI or crawler interpretation:
      Start with <a href="/ai-reading-guide/">AI Reading Guide</a>.
    </p>

    <p>
      For public surface orientation:
      Start with <a href="/public-surface-map/">Public Surface Map</a> and
      <a href="/document-types/">Document Types</a>.
    </p>

    <p>
      For system orientation:
      Start with <a href="/about/">About</a> and <a href="/surfaces/">Entry Surfaces</a>.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Public Surfaces</h2>

    <p>
      Meta-Writing Ecology can be entered through fiction, system documents,
      corpus-facing materials, and public publication records. These surfaces do
      not replace the system architecture. They provide different points of
      access to the same recursive language ecology.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Current Status</h2>

    <p class="note">
      This site is the public surface for Meta-Writing Ecology. It does not
      contain the full working corpus, non-public source structure, or
      non-public working layers.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
